host_about:
Going someplace new is always exciting. And what would that adventure be without a great place to lay your head at the end of the day? That is where I come in!

As an avid traveler myself, I know how the little things can set the pace for a new experience! You want something hospitable and inviting to give you a remarkable experience that no one else can give you. A heated pool, or jacuzzi at the end of the day to relax in, or a nice meal within walking distance? Down to beds that cozy and homily. Sounds good? Well, you have come to the right place.

We offer handpicked accommodations in remarkable properties for a  top-notch experience with a few added extras. As well as tips, recommendations, and 24/7 customer support to make sure that your experience is the best it can be!

In roughly 9 years I've had ~7,300 total guests, through Airbnb and other services.

Why Us
With over 25 years of combined experience managing South Maui vacation condos in the Kihei, Wailea and Makena areas, we have earned our reputation as experts in Hawaii vacations. No one knows Maui like we do. It's the rare combination of quality and service that sets Ali'i Resorts apart. We work hard to elevate our brand to be the top vacation rental company on Maui. We maintain our 5 star Trip Advisor rating by keeping a full staff who strives to exceed your expectations for escape, and deliver your vacation accommodations with ease and satisfaction. We are your personal concierge and will work with you prior to your arrival to plan a range of services, activities, experiences, and excursions - be it a week of action and adventure or a complete relaxation. host_about:
Aloha to my future guests, 

 A little about me, I clean other condos around Waikiki and my leisure time is going to the beach for a quick swim before the sunrise, and go the Ala Wai community garden to tend for my veggies and fruit trees, and in the evening I walk my cat (Ziggy) and don't worry, the studio is pet free. 

I live close by, if you need anything, call/text/email, or use the Airbnb message, I will have my son deliver to you. Aloha and have a beautiful vacation!

name: Island Paradise Living Next to Beach!

Westin Ka’anapali ocean resort villa studio
host_about:
Hawaii. Costa Rica. Jamaica. Bahamas. Yellowstone Park, etc... At the end of one trip, I'm just counting until the next excursion somewhere exciting.  I can't live without traveling. It's in my nomadic nature to roam and never stay in one place.  From food to culture to natural wonders, I love and desire the flavors of the world on my tongue, I love and desire to be immersed in a wholly different culture, and I want to see, hear and feel the natural wonders that surround us. With my loving husband and my two boys we travel at every opportunity and we enjoy snowboarding, surfing, sightseeing. We are fond of Hawaii and have been to three of the islands (Oahu, Maui, Kauai) more times than we can count. 
As a Host on AirBnb, we offer where we go and where we have been so we know what our Guests might experience during their stay. As a result, we have the highest confidence that our Guests' stay will be a truly wonderful experience. 

Aloha and Mahalo,
Abby Heo

host_about: I am from Kailua, OAHU (not Kona) Hawaii.  I live in the house half-time, in which there is one other room available at various times.  It is a large house with lanais (porches) on the side, with a swimming pool in back, extensive flower gardens, nicely landscaped.  I am a psychologist with my own Wellness Center in Kailua - check my website at (Website hidden by Airbnb) for more information on me.  The house has cold AC (split AC, separate controls in each room, solar powered), solar hot water, 4 bathrooms, and no pets.  I am healthy, do not smoke, and do not drink alcohol.  I cannot accept intoxicated renters - a little tipsy is fine but not inebriated.  Neither smoking nor candles are allowed in the house or on the property.

host_about: Aloha, I'm a long time Hawaii resident (17+ years) and I love these magical islands!  I also love Airbnb and the flexibility and unique experiences it helps us provide each other across our beautiful planet. I have stayed in many Airbnb's around the world and also hosted many here in Hawaii. I operate "Pahoa Village Hostel" - a small, boutique style hostel right in Historic Downtown Pahoa on the Big Island. I’m also an experienced and highly rated Realtor with my company "Turquoise Hawaii Real Estate" so I can help you buy or sell property too. I also love volunteering locally, designing, building, renovation, art projects, beaches, waterfalls, vegan food, animals and traveling.  Come visit the Puna District and see all the beautiful sights that goddess "Pele" has created like lava, black sand beaches, hot springs, steam vents, craters, lava tubes, jungles and more !

name: Bamboo Canopy with Shared Kitchen and Bath
host_about: Iris and Zach met on Iris' native "Island of "Magic" in Brazil.  They are organic farmers, wellness advocates, and avid foodies. Their passion is to live sustainably in community,  a return to the village model. As directors of Gingerhill Farm Retreat on the Big Island, they host guests from all over the world who come to learn how to grow and cook the healthiest foods and join them in physical training, yoga, and meditation. Over the past 7 years, they have developed a world-class seed-to-fork kitchen, Here, their rotating staff of international chefs prepares exquisite, nutrient-dense meals using the freshest local ingredients available. Produce from their gardens and orchards. Sustainably-raised meat and wild fish from their farmer and fisherman friends. Come try the Gingerhill Farm Retreat lifestyle and see if it doesn't agree with you. Namastê.

host_about:
I love to travel and discover new cultures. I believe there is a lot to learn from simply interacting with people from different backgrounds, who may have grown up in a much different setting. Different values and opinions can lead us to better develop our own conclusions and perspectives in life. That's one of the reasons I love Airbnb and the sharing economy! name: Room in 3BR house in Maui
host_about:
Lisa is a local girl who's an adventurous traveler, enjoys meeting people from all over the world, is environmentally conscious, a total animal lover, and likes being outdoors & doing sports.

Naoise's an Irish guy who likes traveling & the great outdoors too, but also has a love for art, music, movies, social media and fashion.

Our little boy Nainoa is 5 yrs old now and still loves meeting all the guests!  He  spends a lot of time outdoors going beach, and recently started fishing and doing some mountain biking.

We have a new baby girl Lilinoe who just turned one in 2017.  She is adorable and has the cutest personality!  She's more shy than her brother when meeting new people but is very playful after warming up!

Kea is a Japanese Spitz who just likes running around off the leash somewhere outside and eating really good food!  She loves people too!  

Together, when we have the time, we have fun taking guests to our favorite spots on Maui or enjoy having them over for a hibachi (BBQ)!

name: *Free Master Room w/ Purchase
host_about:
Aloha! 
We are Delamarie & Kepeli Robbins. 
Really quick statement we have to say....

In Hawaii, unfortunately, we have homeless people everywhere. 
across the street of our apartments is a handicap living situation and although they live in the building, they enjoy the fresh air outside and like hanging out in the parking lot. They're honestly the nicer people here in Hawaii, although you may think they're homeless.  We do ask you not to judge these sweet souls. 

We are a happily married couple with grown children and have adopted a baby boy. Hunter is now 8 years old.  We have 18 beautiful grandchildren, 2 fur babies, *Bugsie and KalaPuna, who live upstairs and do not share common areas, 3 kitty cats, Mainge,   Boots and Butters who lives outside......
We are competitive bodybuilders and have our own private training center. We also have the best supplements money can buy.  

Smoking in designated area only.  No smoking in or by our house or apartments 

We have three locations....
1.) Our home.... it is bi level, so our guests have lots of privacy as well as we do.  
With a private fenced-in yard and an amazing swimming pool, you can have a great time here without even leaving the yard. 

2.) Our apartments offer a full kitchen and bath. 

Both our home and apartments are centrally located, and 7-10 minutes away from the airport is perfect for anyone with or without a vehicle. 
Bus stop literally a 2-minute walk away. 
We have kayaks and surfboards that you can use free of charge. Have lots of advice too -

*** Private rooms with a shared bathroom and common areas.
*** Our K suite unit is completely private.  
We use scented laundry detergent and have plugins when available.
3.) Up country...total country vibe away from the hustle and bustle. Cooler place

One of the questions that's asked is, "What are 5 things you can't live without?"
Honestly, the answer to that is simple 
1. God
2. My husband/ family 
3. Trust
4. Health
5. Happiness 

We have worked long and hard and now do a lot of traveling, so we leave our hard-working assistant, Kevin, to help you with all of your needs when we are not here. 
At our home......
Just FYI, NO AIR CONDITIONING or KITCHEN. TOTALLY FENCED IN YARD MEANING YOU'LL HAVE TO OPEN AND CLOSE GATE WHEN LEAVING AND ARRIVING. PULL UP ONTO THE SIDE OF ROAD PUT YOUR FLASHERS ON SLIDE GATE OPEN. SAME WHEN LEAVING at our home.

At our apartments......
Our second location is located above our gym and has FULL KITCHEN and a bath. still NO AIR-CONDITIONING.  Free coffee and tea. Please Park on the right side of the building.

Each room offers different options, so read it carefully.

 Thank you for your consideration.

name: Kamaaina Staycation
host_about:
I have relocated to the Big Island from Colorado, but have lived in many places.  One of which was Oahu many years ago, and I have returned to Hawaii to be with my eldest son and his lovely wife.

My hobbies include portrait art, and I find it's always rewarding to provide people with portraits of their loved ones, including pets.  I taught myself to use pastels which is a beautiful soft medium for capturing precious memories. 

My occupation for many years was clinical support for Home Health Care, but I have always cleaned and organized for fun and profit!  Before that, I worked with middle school children in a charter school environment, teaching them how to clean and maintain their school.  I found them to be very responsive to guidance and learning, gaining respect for themselves and others.

All the skills I've developed seemed to translate quite nicely into being an Airbnb Host.  It is so rewarding when people leave happy and pleased with their stay!

host_about:
I'm a veteran of the US NAVY; served from 1971 - '73. For most of my time in New Orleans, I managed nightclubs in the French Quarter. Also, owned and operated a Personal Trainer business.
I've operated my travel business with AIRBNB since 2008.
I do my best to accommodate all my guests, respond to all inquiries as soon as possible, answer any and all questions, and provide them with the most accurate, up-to-date information about the resorts, and the surrounding areas.
And, I try to give the most economical rates.

host_about: We love travel, music, dance, family, growing food for ourselves and our community, sharing horse wisdom and skills with keiki and horse enthusiasts,  living in harmony with the Aina, and continually learning and growing with this beautiful Hawaiian community.  We are thankful to be living on 15 epic acres, pouring our hearts and souls into developing our organic gardens, orchards, medicinal herbal patches, forging pathways to our waterfalls and secret healing garden and spa.  We co-create with master artists, musicians and healers to realize our vision of providing a peaceful and inspiring landscape for earth travelers to come, rest, be nourished in so many ways and leave refreshed, inspired and hopefully with a deeper appreciation and love of this magical place we call home.

name: Private Room w/ Shared Bath in Hilo w/ Garden View
King 1124
host_about:
Aloha! 
We are Delamarie & Kepeli Robbins. 
Really quick statement we have to say....

In Hawaii, unfortunately, we have homeless people everywhere. 
across the street of our apartments is a handicap living situation and although they live in the building, they enjoy the fresh air outside and like hanging out in the parking lot. They're honestly the nicer people here in Hawaii, although you may think they're homeless.  We do ask you not to judge these sweet souls. 

We are a happily married couple with grown children and have adopted a baby boy. Hunter is now 8 years old.  We have 18 beautiful grandchildren, 2 fur babies, *Bugsie and KalaPuna, who live upstairs and do not share common areas, 3 kitty cats, Mainge,   Boots and Butters who lives outside......
We are competitive bodybuilders and have our own private training center. We also have the best supplements money can buy.  

Smoking in designated area only.  No smoking in or by our house or apartments 

We have three locations....
1.) Our home.... it is bi level, so our guests have lots of privacy as well as we do.  
With a private fenced-in yard and an amazing swimming pool, you can have a great time here without even leaving the yard. 

2.) Our apartments offer a full kitchen and bath. 

Both our home and apartments are centrally located, and 7-10 minutes away from the airport is perfect for anyone with or without a vehicle. 
Bus stop literally a 2-minute walk away. 
We have kayaks and surfboards that you can use free of charge. Have lots of advice too -

*** Private rooms with a shared bathroom and common areas.
*** Our K suite unit is completely private.  
We use scented laundry detergent and have plugins when available.
3.) Up country...total country vibe away from the hustle and bustle. Cooler place

One of the questions that's asked is, "What are 5 things you can't live without?"
Honestly, the answer to that is simple 
1. God
2. My husband/ family 
3. Trust
4. Health
5. Happiness 

We have worked long and hard and now do a lot of traveling, so we leave our hard-working assistant, Kevin, to help you with all of your needs when we are not here. 
At our home......
Just FYI, NO AIR CONDITIONING or KITCHEN. TOTALLY FENCED IN YARD MEANING YOU'LL HAVE TO OPEN AND CLOSE GATE WHEN LEAVING AND ARRIVING. PULL UP ONTO THE SIDE OF ROAD PUT YOUR FLASHERS ON SLIDE GATE OPEN. SAME WHEN LEAVING at our home.

At our apartments......
Our second location is located above our gym and has FULL KITCHEN and a bath. still NO AIR-CONDITIONING.  Free coffee and tea. Please Park on the right side of the building.

Each room offers different options, so read it carefully.

 Thank you for your consideration.

name: Yoga, foodie, surf B&B
host_about:
I have traveled to several destinations throughout the world on surfing trips. Australia,Barbados, Costa Rica,France, Indonesia,Mexico, Senegal West Africa and Hawaii. I visited Hawaii and stayed with Malia Macnamara mother of famous surfers Garrethttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garrett_McNamara & Liamhttp://encyclopediaofsurfing.com/entries/liam-mcnamara. The seed was planted there and the dream was  to create a travel destination with the benefits of exotic places beaches ,food,leisure, yoga,massage,surf,  and safety in one location . I've done it and it's here. I've created LOHAShttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LOHAS programs for the peaceboathttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peace_Boat. I'm happy to say my most recent travels have taken me to the western U.S. experiencing Burningmanhttp://burningman.org/ & Bhaktifest http://bhaktifest.com/2fest/ it's there where you can see the potential for humanity.   My interests have expanded beyond surfing into  yoga,massage,wellness and slowfood, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slow_Foodpermaculturehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permaculture,arts,music, etc.... 
 Doing what you love and making a living doing it creates an infectious cycle inspiring people to lead happy productive lives while meeting other interesting inspired people . I think life turns into what we wish & create it to be. What do you think?

host_about: Aloha, My name is Kai, I was born and raised on the Big Island and grew up in Kealakekua Bay. I'm an active real estate agent in Hawaii so feel free to ask me questions about real estate if your interested. I am also a DJ, sound system & lighting specialist. I was a kayak tour guide for many years in K-Bay and still work part time as a lifeguard/ tour guide at a private beach club but also own a DJ/ sound & lighting event company that hosts events and parties around the island. I enjoy performing as a DJ at local parties & events and also being a sound technician for live music. I also love surfing, scuba diving, and paddling. I enjoy making new friends and sharing knowledge and adventures with others. A motto I like to live by is "Do what you love, and love what you do!" Looking forward to meeting you! Aloha

name: Hawai'i Sunshine House Ohana Garden Home
host_about:
Dave and I enjoy spending time with family, the great outdoors, and (of course) going for long walks on the beach during sunset.   We enjoy hosting visitors and  want for those who come and stay with us to feel what is like to live in Hawaii! 

We enjoy travelling ourselves and have driven several times across the contiguous United States and Alaska (where we lived for many years), as well as piloted a boat through the beautiful Inside Passage of Southeast Alaska, and traveled Alaska, parts of Canada, and the Western U.S. via motorcycle. We especially enjoy epic canoe trips and local walks, so ask if you have any interest in recommendations there! 

Dave and I have both enjoyed careers in public service and social justice and inclusitivity is very important to both of us--my motto is "pray for peace, but work for justice."  My favorite book is F.A. Worsley's "Shackleton's Boat Journey," and Dave loves "The Lord of the Rings," "Harry Potter," and vintage "Uncle Scrooge" comic books.

host_about: My husband and I have been together for 26 yrs. We came to visit Hawaii over 20yrs ago, fell in love with the islands, sold everything we had and moved! The thought was if we fail, no harm done! I feel blessed every day to call Hawaii home. Although I do miss my family on the mainland, I (we) have our other half with us here, Mother and Father in law moved here 12+ yrs  and my Brother and sister in law just 2+ years ago! Being able to get together every Sunday to cook and enjoy each other is something I don’t take for granted.  Love the ocean, with my favorite past time now which is stand up paddle boarding. I was a Dental Assistant for a total of 18 yrs, then quit to help my husband run his construction company. Never did I think I would be doing a bnb, (always have done long term) but oh how I enjoy it!! Love people and enjoy them seeing the islands for their first time or coming back for more to do something they missed or needs repeating...never can one see it all. I hope you will come and enjoy our little slice of Hawaii here on the west side of the island.

host_about:
Kirpal Meditation and Ecological Center is a half mile from the ocean on the eastern tip of the Big Island of Hawaii, approximately seven miles from the small village of Pahoa. The 10-acre ocean-view property is blessed with average daytime temperatures of 85° F year-round, and 65° F at night, with cool, fragrant trade winds, surrounding tropical flora, including old growth mangoes, nearby swimming, surfing and snorkeling.

This property was once a papaya farm and is now newly planted with bamboo, papaya, palms, banana and many other fruit trees. The octagonal Balinese meditation pavilion is set among shade-trees with an expansive view of the ocean. The island wildlife is all around us – a variety of birds by day and at night there's the pleasant chirping of Coqui frogs – and there are no snakes. Natural wonders include Volcanoes National Park, for lava and crater viewing, volcanically heated warm ponds and steam vents (as outdoor saunas) and other wonders of the lush tropics.

Kmec opened in the summer of 2008 for pre-arranged seasonal meditation retreats and private meditation-vacations on request. Additionally, we would like to extend our welcome to Big Island travelers offering cozy cottages and open air kitchen and bath. We offer daily free meditation instructions and practices at our beautiful Balinese meditation pavillion. Additionally, we offer Yoga and nature tours upon guest's request (donations accepted).

name: Unit 204 Oceanfront studio With A/C!
host_about:
Aloha,
Here at Punahoa Oceanfront Vacation Rental's in Kihei, Maui Hawaii.  We offer Studios, One bedrooms, Two bedrooms, and One Bedroom Penthouses that is Ocean front and located right on the beach!  The amenities we provide in Punahoa is FREE PARKING, FREE WIFI INTERNET ACCESS CODE, & FULLY EQUIPPED KITCHEN / KITCHENETTES.  
Inside the units additional amenities such as:

- Hair dryer, hair shampoo, hair conditioner, beach towels, and beach chairs

-Small cooler for your usage to take out and enjoy/travel beach or long drive around Maui.

-Beach chair & beach towels

On property we have two outside shower stalls to rinse off after enjoying your time at the beach.

We also have a gas barbecue grill on property.

Spectacular sunsets and perfect location for surfer's, stand up paddle boarding, and kayak.  Snorkeling from the Cove beach to Charley Young's beach is a must!  We frequently have visits from tired Honu's (Hawaiian sea turtles) resting on our shores / beach.  

***Please be respectful and DO NOT TOUCH/ FEED/ OR BOTHER THE HAWAIIAN SEA TURTLES & HAWAIIAN MONK SEALS!***

Send us a message or any inquires for additional information, we would love to welcome you to be our guest, stay with us here at Punahoa oceanfront vacation rentals, in Kihei Maui Hawaii!  Aloha nui loa!

- Zaldy 

Within walking distances from Fresh local farmers market and produces, outlets and little boutiques, variety of restaurants and bars, rent stand up paddle boards, boogie boards, and snorkeling gears.  Located right on the beach between Maui's famous Charley Young's beach & The Cove.  Close by Kalama beach park and playground.

name: Pa’ani Ranch Cabin 1
organic queen bed & linens shared bath Hana rd
host_about:
We are Gary & Marianne Callari - 
We offer for rent private rooms in Our 1929 Farm house on Maui, Hawaii and (2) Casita Studios in the Red Rocks of Sedona, Arizona. We love nature, home and family. Our fun and together past time is making great dinners at home. We grow our own food and eat and live a very healthy plant based diet. We go to bed fairly early and we get up early. We have healthy habits and healthy relationships with everyone we come in contact with. An open mind and a positive attitude we believe have been our tools in getting the home and lifestyle we create. We try not to have to many rules and flow with what life presents us. Sometimes we are really good at it! We believe energy follows thought, so if you think you can you can! We love to travel and enjoy meeting people from all over the world. Our travels have brought us to Spain, Italy, Mexico, Thailand and the Caribbean. We use travel guides about food to experience the flavors of live! We have two grown adults that we are very proud of, we honor who they are and the choices they have made and look forward to many more exciting adventures with them. 5 things we can't live without: Great weather, great food a higher consciousness, good organic chocolate and of course an active healthy body! We subscribe to the 4 agreements: Be Impeccable with your word. Don't take anything personally. Don't make assumptions. Always do your best. We wish you Happy Travels and Aloha! Gary and Marianne

name: Organic queen bed w/private entrance shared bath
property_type: Private room in bed and breakfast
host_about:
We are Gary & Marianne Callari - 
We offer for rent private rooms in Our 1929 Farm house on Maui, Hawaii and (2) Casita Studios in the Red Rocks of Sedona, Arizona. We love nature, home and family. Our fun and together past time is making great dinners at home. We grow our own food and eat and live a very healthy plant based diet. We go to bed fairly early and we get up early. We have healthy habits and healthy relationships with everyone we come in contact with. An open mind and a positive attitude we believe have been our tools in getting the home and lifestyle we create. We try not to have to many rules and flow with what life presents us. Sometimes we are really good at it! We believe energy follows thought, so if you think you can you can! We love to travel and enjoy meeting people from all over the world. Our travels have brought us to Spain, Italy, Mexico, Thailand and the Caribbean. We use travel guides about food to experience the flavors of live! We have two grown adults that we are very proud of, we honor who they are and the choices they have made and look forward to many more exciting adventures with them. 5 things we can't live without: Great weather, great food a higher consciousness, good organic chocolate and of course an active healthy body! We subscribe to the 4 agreements: Be Impeccable with your word. Don't take anything personally. Don't make assumptions. Always do your best. We wish you Happy Travels and Aloha! Gary and Marianne

It's an island paradise on a 500 year old farm where the sweet spirit of Hawaii resides.  The farm offers me and my guests, a peaceful, quiet, farm stay on aina (land) that is deeply rooted in the old Hawaiian traditions and ways of Aloha. I danced hula with Halau 'O KeikiAli'i and I grow gourds for making Ipu Heke (gourd implements used by hula dancers). I start most every day with a great swim at one of the many bays in South Kona.

host_about:
My name is Sherry Boonstra-Barbier and I have been living on Maui for the past 30 years. My family and I initially moved here from Chicago, Illinois aiming to escape the cold weather in the "windy city." In doing so, we landed in Lahaina (Hawaiian for "merciless sun") which happens to be the previous capital of the Hawaiian Kingdom. Since I arrived here all those years ago I have been operating a Bed and Breakfast out of my home and have gradually expanded to accommodate different types of travelers ranging from Hostel travelers to luxury estates. I have met many wonderful visitors throughout the years, many of which I have become close friends with. With my thorough expertise about the island of Maui, and decades of experience as a host I am confident I can help you make the most of your stay here in the islands. I look forward to hearing from you.

Aloha,
Sherry

host_about:
First came to Kailua Kona Hi, to compete in the Ironman Triathlon competition, fell in love with the Islands, and stayed. 
Kundalini Yoga teacher, lover of sports: cycling, swimming, running but most of all surfing.
The Big Island of Hawaii -  is a place of great beauty, excellent weather, and many fun activities.
Honolulu offers all city advantages with little noise and pollution. 
The greatest surf breaks are found on the Islands of Hawaii as well as Kite & wind surfing, Golfing, snorkeling, diving, paddling and amazing hikes. 
The Islands of Hawaii are some of the most precious gems on our planet and so is the culture of the 
Hawaiian people their wisdom and knowledge, I feel that It is a great privilege to live here.

name: Oceanview Studio | Pools | Hot Tub | Tennis Courts
host_about:
Vacasa
Vacation Home Management

Vacasa unlocks the possibilities of how we enjoy vacation homes. We take care of managing our homeowners’ vacation houses so they can have peace of mind (and their home when they want to). And our guests book vacations confidently knowing they’re going to find exactly what they’re looking for without any surprises.

Each vacation home is always cared for by our professional local teams who implement our high cleanliness and maintenance values, while the hands-off tasks of vacation rental management--marketing, filing taxes, and maintaining a website--are handled by a specialized central support team. Our passion and focus remain true: to empower our homeowners, guests, and employees to invest in vacation.

name: Relaxing 4 Star Luana Waikiki w/Park View
host_about:
Hi, I am Hiroko. I am originally from Japan and have been living in Hawaii since 2006 when my first daughter was 2 years and a half old. 

I have traveled more than 30 countries so far and the number is still increasing! I have home stayed in US, UK, Spain, Italy, Switzerland and Australia.

Through these experiences, I learned, "when in Rome, do as the Romans do" attitude. This definitely makes it easier to accept whatever happens during the trip and makes it more fun.

I love traveling and meeting new people and culture. When free, I would be happy to assist the guests as much as I can to make their stay memorable. 

2006年、長女が２歳半だった時にハワイに引っ越してきましたヒロコです。旅行が好きで、世界訪れた国は３０カ国を越え、その数はこれからも更に増えていくことでしょう！アメリカ、イギリス、スペイン、イタリア、スイス、オーストラリアでは、ホームステイしていました。
そんな旅行やホームステイの経験から学んだのが、”郷に入っては郷に従う”という姿勢です。これが根本にあると、旅行中に起こる全てのことに寛容になれ、楽しめます。
新しく人と出会うのが好きなので、滞在中時間があれば、ゲストの方にとってハワイ滞在が思い出深いものとなるよう、出来るだけサポートさせて頂きます！

Skyline Views! Work-From-Home Oasis!
Honolulu Panoramic Condo
host_about:
Hi there! I’m Mathilde :-) I’m a civil engineer and I live partly in Hawaii and Norway, & this is my home in Norway. 

It’s a reason why I want to rent out my place here on Airbnb - I truly believe it’s the one of the most beautiful spots in Bergen and would love for people to see and share the same experience as me in the apartment and exploring Bergen 

I’ve previously worked in hospitality and have a good understanding of people’s wants and needs, also in terms of cleanliness. 

A big passion of mine is to travel and experience new cultures, and I’ve stayed in many peoples homes throughout my life as a traveler - & very happy to be able to host people as well. 

Feel free to send me a message with questions before booking, happy to answer all of your questions! :)

host_about:
When you stay at Pacific Monarch, you can experience Honolulu like a local. Nearby you have a wide selection of shops and restaurants, and the neighborhood is very walkable. You’re just two blocks from famous-for-a-reason Waikiki Beach and can easily get to attractions like the Waikiki Aquarium and Honolulu Zoo.

Venturing out from here rewards you with the wonders of Hanauma and Kaneohe bays and so much more. Our front desk staff would love to help you plan inspiring journeys on Oahu.

Going someplace new is always exciting. And what would that adventure be without a great place to lay your head at the end of the day? That is where I come in!

name: Queen Kapiolani Hotel, Premier Ocean View King
Queen Kapiolani Hotel, City View Balcony King
Spectacular Views of Hanalei Bay and Bali Hai 9203
host_about:
Aloha Welcome to Kauai and Hanalei Bay Resort

I was 18 years old when first traveled to Kauai. My sister and I
hiked the Na Pali Coastline trail. I fell in love with Kauai and
hoped that everyone I cared about could come here someday and
experience the love, the beauty and the magic of Kauai. Many
decades later, my husband Steve and I returned here after
raising our kids. That was December 2020. Covid Time. We
stayed in this very condo and both of us felt drawn to this island
in a way that words can’t describe. We have traveled all over the
world, 30 + countries and stayed in hundreds of different
accommodations in our travels. Of all the places we traveled in
the world, Kauai is hands down our favorite place.
Of all the Hawaiian Islands, this garden island is by far our
favorite. When we decided, we were going to buy here, we looked
all over the island and viewed many different condos. We kept
coming back to this lovely condo. This is our favorite part of the
island because of the mountains and stunning beaches. We felt
that we got the best condo in the complex with the best
unobstructed views in Hanalei Bay Resort. . Today, we are beyond
happy to share our little piece of paradise with you. Kauai might
just be the most romantic place on Earth. Everywhere you look is
beautiful! Stunning landscapes, pristine beaches, amazing waves,
beautiful flowers, and unforgettable sunsets. Kauai is steeped in
history and culture. Of course, there is no shortage of things to do
and see. We hope that you find the same magic, love and beauty
that touched our souls and lingers in the air no matter where you
are at in Kauai.

host_about:
Hawaii. Costa Rica. Jamaica. Bahamas. Yellowstone Park, etc... At the end of one trip, I'm just counting until the next excursion somewhere exciting.  I can't live without traveling. It's in my nomadic nature to roam and never stay in one place.  From food to culture to natural wonders, I love and desire the flavors of the world on my tongue, I love and desire to be immersed in a wholly different culture, and I want to see, hear and feel the natural wonders that surround us. With my loving husband and my two boys we travel at every opportunity and we enjoy snowboarding, surfing, sightseeing. We are fond of Hawaii and have been to three of the islands (Oahu, Maui, Kauai) more times than we can count. 
As a Host on AirBnb, we offer where we go and where we have been so we know what our Guests might experience during their stay. As a result, we have the highest confidence that our Guests' stay will be a truly wonderful experience. 

Aloha and Mahalo,
Abby Heo

name: Ali'i Honeymoon Suite
property_type: Private room in bed and breakfast
host_about:
My husband, John and I own the Kauai Banyan Inn, a Kauai bed and breakfast Inn located a few minutes from sunny Poipu Beach.   Years in the making, we have lived on the property since 1976 starting out in an old plantation cottage.  When it burned down we built another small home and then subdivided the property to put in the long driveway into the back portion of the property.

Our beloved family home was designed and built in 1989 with an “old Hawaii” essence to capture the incredible view of Black Mountain and the Pacific ocean beyond.  As our children became young adults and went off to college, every summer or Christmas vacation they would return with their friends.  No one ever wanted to leave.  In fact, after college, all the children eventually came back home, married, started families and built homes on the property.

With a very, large empty "nest", we felt the house and setting so special it should be shared, and that is how Kauai Banyan Inn came to be.  Having been in the hospitality business for 40 years and enjoying the interaction with guests and sharing the beautiful Island with them,  it was a natural transition for us to turn our home into a bed and breakfast inn.  

The Kauai Banyan Inn is a family operation, with daughter-in-laws helping us with the daily operations and our sons and grandsons help with the landscape and property maintenance.

Sustainability is Important to Us
Since 2018, Kauai Banyan Inn is “powered by the sun” with a complete solar system installation, furthering our goal of energy efficiency and sustainability.  We have also been recognized by the National Wildlife Federation as a certified Wildlife Habitat because of our planning, landscape and sustainable gardening practices which support wildlife in finding quality habitat (food, water, cover) and places to raise their young.

Kauai Banyan Inn has been a labor of love for our family for many years.  We look forward to welcoming you with Aloha to this very special place in paradise!

name: Pu'eo Suite
property_type: Private room in bed and breakfast
host_about:
My husband, John and I own the Kauai Banyan Inn, a Kauai bed and breakfast Inn located a few minutes from sunny Poipu Beach.   Years in the making, we have lived on the property since 1976 starting out in an old plantation cottage.  When it burned down we built another small home and then subdivided the property to put in the long driveway into the back portion of the property.

Our beloved family home was designed and built in 1989 with an “old Hawaii” essence to capture the incredible view of Black Mountain and the Pacific ocean beyond.  As our children became young adults and went off to college, every summer or Christmas vacation they would return with their friends.  No one ever wanted to leave.  In fact, after college, all the children eventually came back home, married, started families and built homes on the property.

With a very, large empty "nest", we felt the house and setting so special it should be shared, and that is how Kauai Banyan Inn came to be.  Having been in the hospitality business for 40 years and enjoying the interaction with guests and sharing the beautiful Island with them,  it was a natural transition for us to turn our home into a bed and breakfast inn.  

The Kauai Banyan Inn is a family operation, with daughter-in-laws helping us with the daily operations and our sons and grandsons help with the landscape and property maintenance.

Sustainability is Important to Us
Since 2018, Kauai Banyan Inn is “powered by the sun” with a complete solar system installation, furthering our goal of energy efficiency and sustainability.  We have also been recognized by the National Wildlife Federation as a certified Wildlife Habitat because of our planning, landscape and sustainable gardening practices which support wildlife in finding quality habitat (food, water, cover) and places to raise their young.

Kauai Banyan Inn has been a labor of love for our family for many years.  We look forward to welcoming you with Aloha to this very special place in paradise!

name: Family Friendly Home

host_about:
Aloha friends! We are the owners of the Lava Pond Lodge™. 
It has been an incredible journey the last couple of years, and I have met hundreds of travelers from all over the world. I absolutely love exchanging travel stories with our guests as I have been an avid traveler for many, many years having been to over 36 countries on 6 continents. It has been a pleasure meeting so many different people. I look forward to meeting you when you visit us.

name: Marriott's Kaua‘i Beach Club | 1 Bedroom
Charming private bedroom+private bathroom+wetbar
Marriott’s Ko Olina vacation club 1 bedroom
host_about:
Hawaii. Costa Rica. Jamaica. Bahamas. Yellowstone Park, etc... At the end of one trip, I'm just counting until the next excursion somewhere exciting.  I can't live without traveling. It's in my nomadic nature to roam and never stay in one place.  From food to culture to natural wonders, I love and desire the flavors of the world on my tongue, I love and desire to be immersed in a wholly different culture, and I want to see, hear and feel the natural wonders that surround us. With my loving husband and my two boys we travel at every opportunity and we enjoy snowboarding, surfing, sightseeing. We are fond of Hawaii and have been to three of the islands (Oahu, Maui, Kauai) more times than we can count. 
As a Host on AirBnb, we offer where we go and where we have been so we know what our Guests might experience during their stay. As a result, we have the highest confidence that our Guests' stay will be a truly wonderful experience. 

Aloha and Mahalo,
Abby Heo

name: Isle Of You Naturally Farm Retreat
host_about:
a decade ago,  my husband bailed on the mainland and all its stress to buy a 70 acre farm on the Big Island near Pahoa. We are a working farm located on the east side of the island of Hawaii, about 30 min south of Hilo on the Puna Coast, close to the quaint village of Pahoa.
We spend our days tending to gardens, the fruit orchards, maybe a day at the local black sand beach called Kehena, playing volleyball or just watching sunsets.
Our guests tend to be outdoor types who love to be in nature.  We invite you up for coffee if you'd like or you can hang by yourself and we'll ignore you if that's what you want.  Then you'll be in your own little paradise and only contacting us when you need info or want to chat.
A couple of mottos to live by include:
'Ua mau ke ea o ka'aina i ka pono o Hawaii'  -- The life of the land in Hawaii is preserved in righteousness.

host_about:
Aloha!
A little about myself; 
I moved to the Big Island in 1993 from Guam after serving a short stint in the USCG during the Golf War,  then worked as an acute care nurse at our local Hilo hospital for the last 22 years.  

Ive remained mesmerized by this island’s amazing natural beauty, diverse ecosystems, terrains, and love the laid back lifestyle it provides which easily translated into me transforming my house to one I can happily and proudly share with those seeking to explore and experience this amazing island in a relaxed home setting.  

I'm originally  from the Micronesian Island of Yap,  known for its pristine water, manta ray dives ( check out the world-famous  Yap Divers ) and  its colorful and spirited bamboo war dance performed by bare chested natives in lion clothes and grass skirts, something I grew up doing.   
I embrace  cultural diversity and truly enjoy meeting people from all walks of life and all regions in the world.  I take pride in my house and the service that I provide my guests. I value my precious 'free' time by sneaking in sporadic reading here and there  and enjoying the outdoors; camping, hiking, swimming, kayaking, paddle board, and gardening, but most of all, I love traveling and looking forward to seeing a lot more of this amazing world we live in and experience different cultures along the way.

I’m always striving for a balanced lifestyle; healthy living through heath conscious cooking utilizing locally grown, ( a lot are my own home grown) produce, keeping physically active, and inner peace and serenity.   

I look forward to meeting you and I'm excited to host another amazing adventurous soul seeking to experience the Big Island of Hawaii!  

Welcome & E Komo Mai!

Diana

name: The Perfect Naturist Hideaway Cabin
host_about:
a decade ago,  my husband bailed on the mainland and all its stress to buy a 70 acre farm on the Big Island near Pahoa. We are a working farm located on the east side of the island of Hawaii, about 30 min south of Hilo on the Puna Coast, close to the quaint village of Pahoa.
We spend our days tending to gardens, the fruit orchards, maybe a day at the local black sand beach called Kehena, playing volleyball or just watching sunsets.
Our guests tend to be outdoor types who love to be in nature.  We invite you up for coffee if you'd like or you can hang by yourself and we'll ignore you if that's what you want.  Then you'll be in your own little paradise and only contacting us when you need info or want to chat.
A couple of mottos to live by include:
'Ua mau ke ea o ka'aina i ka pono o Hawaii'  -- The life of the land in Hawaii is preserved in righteousness.
'Aloha mai no, aloha aku; o ka huhu ka mea e ola ' ole ai' ---When love is given, love should be returned; anger is the thing that gives no life.

My passion is taking people out to swim with the dolphins, which I have facilitated for 22 years as well as facilitating swims with the South Pacific Humpback Whales in Tonga. I love animals and do whatever I can to save them. Being in Nature is important to me and here on the Big Island we are surrounded, it is Paradise. 
My home is inviting and welcoming to those who would like to come and relax and feel the healing energies that my environment offers you. I look forward to meeting you and having you stay. If you would like dolphin swims I am available to bring you to these amazing animals, it is something you will never forget! Blessings to you~~~~Celeste

name: Private Room in Honolulu
host_about:
Aloha!

I’m an active duty military, on my early 30’s. I like a  quiet and peaceful environment. I usually just watch tv in my room or at work. I’m looking for a long term renter.

name: Centrally located, 1 bdrm with shared bath in home
property_type: Private room in bed and breakfast
host_about: I am a retired woman who has lived in Hawaii for 40  years and can offer great advice as to what to see and do while you are in Honolulu.  I live with my cat Santiago who is very friendly and loves Airbnb guests.  I have worked in Social Services here in Honolulu, have a Master's Degree in Cultural Anthropology and love to travel.  I speak some French and a bit of Spanish and love meeting people from all over the world.  I welcome you to my home.

name: Wyndham Waikiki BCH Walk 1Br STE
Kona Hawaiian Resort 2BR Sleeps6
host_about: Hi, I'm Joy! I'm excited for you to check out my listings and discover all the places you can go! I would love to be a part of your travel journey, as its one of my favorite things in life! My parents had us on adventures starting at a very young age and I thankfully got to see and experience so many wonderful and breathtaking places! I love taking my family on those same adventures now and would be so excited to help you plan out some of yours! Please feel free to reach out with any questions you might have, I am representing owners of the underutilized timeshares that might be just perfect for your next journey! If there is anything you're looking for and don't see in the listings please let me know and a lot of times I can help track down exactly what you are looking for! Can't wait to start planning your next adventure with you! Happy Travels!

name: Private Bungalow (Hula Hale)
host_about:
We have been blessed to call North Kohala, Hawai'i home for over a decade. This is where we raise our family and run our farm and nonprofit, HIP Agriculture. As educators, we work with island youth around issues of food sovereignty, farmer training, and building resiliency. At Starseed Ranch under HIP ag,  we host farm field trips for local school groups and farmer training workshops.

Starseed Ranch has a vibrant history of sustainability and community, and we are honored to serve as stewards. This land has always held a special place in our hearts as we were married here in 2011, and have returned many times over the years to spend time with the previous owners, Jyoti and Andre. We have been hosting overnight lodging and special events since 2019,  and are excited to welcome more people to this beautiful and sacred place. Please look around and let us know if you have any questions. We look forward to hosting you at Starseed Ranch soon!

 Dash & Erika Kuhr,
 Starseed Ranch Events

name: Private bedroom and bathroom

Hi, my name is Jessika.  I’m here to go above and beyond to ensure all our guests enjoy their stay and to provide the best quality customer service possible.

I like to spend my free time with my husband and kids and enjoy our beautiful city has to offer.  We look forward to hosting you and providing you the best Airbnb experience.

property_type: Private room in bed and breakfast
host_about:
こんにちわ
ゆきみそうのKIMIKOです。
 私はカリフォルニアからここハワイ島に2009年に移住してきました。

 パートナーの姉であります小田まゆみのライフスタイルに感動し
自給自足を目指しているうちに気がつけば、民宿ゆきみそうを始めていました。

  今では果物、野菜などはできる限り自分で作ったものを提供できる様にもなりました。
そしてまた、ここで知り合えた人達からいろいろ沢山の事も学び、
 まだまだ毎日が出会いであり、発見であります。

   ハワイ島に親戚の家があるような感じでお使いいただけることを願っています。

   いつの日かお会いできます日を楽しみにしています。
     いっぱいの愛と感謝を込めて
              MAHALO

name: Indulge in Home Like Comfort! 2 Relaxing Units
host_about:
Going someplace new is always exciting. And what would that adventure be without a great place to lay your head at the end of the day? That is where I come in!

As an avid traveler myself, I know how the little things can set the pace for a new experience! You want something hospitable and inviting to give you a remarkable experience that no one else can give you. A heated pool, or jacuzzi at the end of the day to relax in, or a nice meal within walking distance? Down to beds that cozy and homily. Sounds good? Well, you have come to the right place.

We offer handpicked accommodations in remarkable properties for a  top-notch experience with a few added extras. As well as tips, recommendations, and 24/7 customer support to make sure that your experience is the best it can be!

name: Large Sunroom, Poolside
host_about: I am from Kailua, OAHU (not Kona) Hawaii.  I live in the house half-time, in which there is one other room available at various times.  It is a large house with lanais (porches) on the side, with a swimming pool in back, extensive flower gardens, nicely landscaped.  I am a psychologist with my own Wellness Center in Kailua - check my website at (Website hidden by Airbnb) for more information on me.  The house has cold AC (split AC, separate controls in each room, solar powered), solar hot water, 4 bathrooms, and no pets.  I am healthy, do not smoke, and do not drink alcohol.  I cannot accept intoxicated renters - a little tipsy is fine but not inebriated.  Neither smoking nor candles are allowed in the house or on the property.

name: Cool Coffee Shack Farm Stay - Comfort in Nature

name: Private Bungalow (Jungalow Hale)
host_about:
We have been blessed to call North Kohala, Hawai'i home for over a decade. This is where we raise our family and run our farm and nonprofit, HIP Agriculture. As educators, we work with island youth around issues of food sovereignty, farmer training, and building resiliency. At Starseed Ranch under HIP ag,  we host farm field trips for local school groups and farmer training workshops.

Starseed Ranch has a vibrant history of sustainability and community, and we are honored to serve as stewards. This land has always held a special place in our hearts as we were married here in 2011, and have returned many times over the years to spend time with the previous owners, Jyoti and Andre. We have been hosting overnight lodging and special events since 2019,  and are excited to welcome more people to this beautiful and sacred place. Please look around and let us know if you have any questions. We look forward to hosting you at Starseed Ranch soon!

 Dash & Erika Kuhr,
 Starseed Ranch Events

name: Beachcomber: Lanai, AC, and Short Walk to Beach!
host_about:
Hello! My name is Sri and I am the owner of several vacation rentals in both San Francisco and Hawaii. I am incredibly blessed to call these two beautiful places my home and to be able to share my properties with travelers from all over the world. 

I currently reside in San Francisco, but my second home is in Hawaii, where I spend a lot of time with my family. We are thankful to have the opportunity to experience the beauty and culture of both places, and I am excited to share this experience with our guests. 

Our vacation rental properties in San Francisco offer the perfect blend of city living and relaxation, with easy access to all the city has to offer, including popular attractions, restaurants, and shopping. 
Our Hawaii properties are located in some of the most beautiful spots on the island, allowing you to truly relax and enjoy the tropical paradise.

Being able to provide vacation rental properties in both San Francisco and Hawaii is truly a dream come true for me. 
I take great pride in ensuring that our guests have the best possible experience when staying in our properties and I am always available to help with anything they need. 
I believe that everyone should have the opportunity to experience the beauty and wonder of these two amazing places and I am grateful to be able to help make that happen. Thank you for considering our properties and I hope to welcome you soon!

We both have had many worldly adventures that allowed us to stay at lots of cool airbnbs which helped us to create our own oasis here to share with others :) I’m originally from a small town in Minnesota but have spent the last couple of years in Seattle studying Medical Anthropology & Global Health at the University of Washington Seattle and whitewater rafting. name: Treehouse! Best views of Kaneohe Bay, 30 days+
Twin/Quiet room near Hanauma Bay
Mangolay, a Garden of Eden in Puna
host_about:
Mangolay is back!  We survived a very close call with the lava, as it spilled over the hill behind us, and came within 1/4 mile of the house.  
  We lost our hot pond, and tide pools for snorkeling to the eruption, but we now have a brand new black sand beach nearby.  It is a one mile hike, but well worth it.  It is said we have up to 5 more beaches as well, but until the lava is completely cooled, there are no trails to them yet.
     I share the property with 2 dogs.  Felicia who is very friendly, and Tulu Hound, who thinks he is the head of security.  Once he realizes you belong here, he quickly warms up.  The house was designed by the late Dennis Preston Davis, an architect specializing in solar powered homes. I am an avid gardener and have a large collection of tropical plants. I have traveled the world extensively, experiencing its diverse cultures and natural wonders, and it is reflected in my home. Mangolay features a large collection of unique art and crafts from around the world. I enjoy living in Hawaii and sharing  experiences and recommendations with the guests. Meeting new people and sharing conversations is very rewarding, especially when you live in a remote place.
It now takes about 15 minutes to get to Pahoa Town.

name: LOLIA Eco-Village | All-Inclusive EAT & SLEEP B24
host_about: Hello, We are an eco-village retreat center that focuses on yoga, meditation, permaculture and personal growth courses. Our site is solar powered, and 100% of our water is provided by rainfall. The grounds have many organic fruit growing such as papaya, banana, coconut, citrus, macadamia nut, avocado, mango, and pineapple. We are walking distance to the ocean and have a gorgeous chemical-free cedar hot tub. We love hosting new people from all over the world in this unique setting.

host_about:
Welcome to wonderful Hood River!  I had always wanted to live in Hood River and finally made that happen by buying "Hood River Suites & Extended Stay Apartments" in 1999.  

Hood  River Suites & Extended Stay Apartments were a 9 unit 1-bedroom apartment building that I converted into vacation rentals.  Located at 709 Cascade Ave (7th/Cascade) in the heart of downtown Hood River.  I also rent my house at 922 Oak St out when I am not using it.   More pictures and area info are available on the site hoodriversuites 

My properties are legal rentals registered in the City of Hood River and I pay the 8% city and 1.8% state transient lodging tax.  My rates are higher and odd numbers because I include the tax in the rate.  

Example:  $141 per night is $130 per night plus $11.70 tax but air bnb won't list it as 141.70.

こんにちわ
ゆきみそうのKIMIKOです。
 私はカリフォルニアからここハワイ島に2009年に移住してきました。

 パートナーの姉であります小田まゆみのライフスタイルに感動し
自給自足を目指しているうちに気がつけば、民宿ゆきみそうを始めていました。

  今では果物、野菜などはできる限り自分で作ったものを提供できる様にもなりました。
そしてまた、ここで知り合えた人達からいろいろ沢山の事も学び、
 まだまだ毎日が出会いであり、発見であります。

   ハワイ島に親戚の家があるような感じでお使いいただけることを願っています。

   いつの日かお会いできます日を楽しみにしています。
     いっぱいの愛と感謝を込めて
              MAHALO

host_about: I grew up on Oahu, lived on the mainland for many years, and returned to Hawaii  in 2008. My husband is retired and I work from home. Our house has a nice view of Hilo Bay and Mauna Kea, and when I'm not working, I'm tending to the garden, talking a walk up to Rainbow Falls or gone for a swim. As a once frequent business traveler, I understand the importance of finding a quiet, restful place to decompress, relax and power-down after a long day.  My brother used to live in the studio space downstairs, when he moved out, we decided to invite AirBnB guests to take advantage of the room and our proximity to the hospital, University, and downtown. E komo mai!

host_about:
Aloha! We are originally from Washington State where we lived in a small town. One day we decided to sell everything and move to Kona and start a vacation rental. Our goal has been to make the place a home away from home for travelers. We want everyone to feel comfortable and enjoy their stay in Kona. We have met so many interesting and wonderful people along the way as well that have made it such a great adventure.

We like to spend time at the beach, snorkel, boogie board, hike and go site seeing to name just a few. One of our favorite times during the year is Iron Man. There are so many things to do in Kona this is definitely the place for us. We hope you come visit us soon.

1br Westin Ka'anapali Ocean Resort Villa timeshare
host_about:
Welcome to wonderful Hood River!  I had always wanted to live in Hood River and finally made that happen by buying "Hood River Suites & Extended Stay Apartments" in 1999.  

Hood  River Suites & Extended Stay Apartments were a 9 unit 1-bedroom apartment building that I converted into vacation rentals.  Located at 709 Cascade Ave (7th/Cascade) in the heart of downtown Hood River.  I also rent my house at 922 Oak St out when I am not using it.   More pictures and area info are available on the site hoodriversuites 

My properties are legal rentals registered in the City of Hood River and I pay the 8% city and 1.8% state transient lodging tax.  My rates are higher and odd numbers because I include the tax in the rate.  

Example:  $141 per night is $130 per night plus $11.70 tax but air bnb won't list it as 141.70.

Thank you for coming to my world . I live in San Jose CA and finished my MBA degree here.  I am a realtor,  investor , world solo traveler  , diver ,free diver , wildlife photographer and airbnb host....  I love my job and love to share and make new friends . Each home I have here are presenting different life style living . Which one is my favorite ? Great question but I don't have an answer . Because they offer very different life time experiences.   Love them all and they are all my babies and all can be my retirement home in the terms of my life . But one thing in common is  they are all  "Tropical style and  island living  ". Because  I love warm area.  I would love to invite you to come and share my life style and homes with you . It will be my honor to be your host and make my creation more meaningful and memorable . Making you happy is my mission ! 
Hope to see you soon . Thank for reading this far, cheers...

name: Convenient locale! beachgoers, shoppers, foodies
host_about: If you are looking for a quiet place to get away in a busy city, then we have the spot for you. We are located at the largest mall in Honolulu with plenty of eateries only a few steps from our location. One of the most famous beaches in Honolulu is within sight and it has the most magical sunsets you will ever experience. Our Airbnb is a hotel unit located in the famous Ala Moana Hotel, where you have access to spa, pool, workout and fine dining all located on the hotel grounds. We look forward to your visit and helping you experience Aloha.

Going someplace new is always exciting. And what would that adventure be without a great place to lay your head at the end of the day? That is where I come in!

As an avid traveler myself, I know how the little things can set the pace for a new experience! You want something hospitable and inviting to give you a remarkable experience that no one else can give you. A heated pool, or jacuzzi at the end of the day to relax in, or a nice meal within walking distance? Down to beds that cozy and homily. Sounds good? Well, you have come to the right place.

host_about:
My wife Lisa and I are a loving and laid back couple. I have been on the island for 20 years and my wife was born and raised here.  We are animal lovers and have a mature dog Milo and an adolescent dog Roman who are allowed inside the common area of the house on the bottom floor. This area includes the living room and kitchen. The Tropical room is also located on this first floor.  We have a menagerie of other animals too! 3 cats who live outdoors...Leo our orange lover boy, Lola our newest playful kitty and Koa who is an energetic crazy but loveable cat and Avery our little bunny rabbit.   

I have created a lush landscaped orchard environment around our 6 bedroom house, by planting almost 200 trees/flowering plants. We enjoy meeting guests who travel from all over the world and learning about them and their culture. 

My wife and I live here full time along with my mother who's more part time.  Cathy is a busy bee and always has a full schedule of events planned for herself around the community.   We enjoy meeting our guests, but we give you your space and also enjoy our space as well.

name: Island Room for Long Stay
host_about:
Aloha kākou! Salut! こんにちは! I am a local "hapa" (half Okinawan, half French).

I started out as an RN, wandered into the U. Of Hawai'i faculty system, and then... fell in love with teaching, learning, and educational design; especially alternative and web-based solutions.

My passions are endless: mixed media art, reading, technology, knitting, power tools, gardening, skiing, hiking, biking, camping, travel, volunteerism, baseball, Broadway, cooking, entertaining and TGIF's!

After spending most of my life in the islands and in empty-nest mode, I am designing the second half to explore mainland opportunities and travel more. 

I have always loved having a "home" in the islands to welcome mainland, inter-island, and international family and friends. Air B&B is the perfect opportunity to being able to welcome and host them in our now empty rooms, enabling everyone to enjoy all of what we islanders love about living here.

With Hawai'i's new short stay accommodation laws, we are only able to host 30-day or longer reservations. However, this does not affect our typical long-staying guests who come to the island for graduate program rotations, intern or externships, travel medical staff contracts, sabbaticals, grandparent month-long visits, etc.

Our goal is to provide a turnkey furnished and supplied island home for your 30-99 day time on O'ahu so that all you need to fly over with are your carryon of clothes and cell phone.

Please know, under the current pandemic circumstances, we are following all the federal, state, county, city and AirBnB mandates and policies along with our own home requirements to help all of us be good global and Honolulu citizens. Please send me a inquiry to run by your plans with me to consult with the most current policies.

host_about:
I'm a single retired police detective from Oahu. For 16 years I offered horseback rides on Oahu, but moved to the Big Island with my horses when the ranch lease recently expired. 

Originally from the Midwest, I did a stint in the military, which brought me to the islands in 1978.  My education includes an AA in Foreign Languages, a BA in Psychology and completion of a Master's program in Guidance & Counseling. 
 
I'm a Christian, who believes the good Lord brought me to this fantastic place.
I love the serene beauty and quiet of this location, and since the house is much larger than one person needs, wish to share it with traveling guests,  who will also enjoy its comfort and fabulous views.  Besides that, the horses still "eat like horses", even though they are no longer earning their keep!

As a pet lover, I would prefer folks who also like animals.  Because I have so many, I don't have a chance to travel much, although in the past I did get the opportunity to visit Spain, France, Switzerland  and England.  I was stationed in Florida & CA as well as Hawaii while in the military.   

I enjoy a variety of books and movies, preferably well-written and thought-provoking.  A good comedy is always appreciated, as well.  My social life now is mostly a weekly ladies' luncheon and music nights at the Fifties Café.

host_about:
ALOHA & WELCOME,

Thank you very much for viewing our various accommodations. Our accommodations are located along the lush and tropical Hamakua Coast, 15 miles north of Hilo.
I am  Akiko Masuda, a 3rd generation Japanese woman, born in Honolulu in the 40’s, long before freeways, shopping malls, email, Blackberrys, and cell phones. I have been a writer of children's books, student of tai chi, hula, and zen meditation,  I am a storyteller, hostess, housekeeper, and love caring for our gardens and fruit trees with our weedwhacker and leaf blower. I am the president of the WAILEA VILLAGE HISTORIC PRESERVATION COMMUNITY. I have been living in Wailea Village since' 91, and at that time, was the first person  to buy in this quiet, peaceful country village in 35 years.  Please come and discover the peace and kindness here.

name: 2 queen bed studio Palms at Waikiki

host_about:
Ali'i is Hawaiian for "royalty," and we strive to live up to our name by giving each of our guests the royal treatment. Amenities include:

Pre-check in condo inspection by our attentive staff
Personal "Aloha" upon your arrival
Full concierge and activity service
Gift pack of elite bath amenities
Luxury bed linens and towels

Why Us
With over 25 years of combined experience managing South Maui vacation condos in the Kihei, Wailea and Makena areas, we have earned our reputation as experts in Hawaii vacations. No one knows Maui like we do. It's the rare combination of quality and service that sets Ali'i Resorts apart. We work hard to elevate our brand to be the top vacation rental company on Maui. We maintain our 5 star Trip Advisor rating by keeping a full staff who strives to exceed your expectations for escape, and deliver your vacation accommodations with ease and satisfaction. We are your personal concierge and will work with you prior to your arrival to plan a range of services, activities, experiences, and excursions - be it a week of action and adventure or a complete relaxation. Come see us soon and let our ohana create a vacation of dreams for you and your family.

name: Maui Star Dome - Includes Skylight Loft Bedroom
host_about:
Diane and I have lived mostly on Maui since we came here on our Honeymoon in 1978.  At one time we both worked at the Observatory atop Mt. Haleakala. More recently, we both worked for the County of Maui, Diane at Finance and me at Parks and Rec.
Our son recently graduated from the University of Central Florida.  All three of us are musicians as avocation, primarily at churches and youth groups.
We discovered AirBnB while planning our summer trip to the Pacific Northwest and very much enjoyed staying at various BnB's.

name: Beautiful 2 Bedroom 2 Bath-Valley Isle Resort #803
host_about:
Ali'i is Hawaiian for "royalty," and we strive to live up to our name by giving each of our guests the royal treatment. Amenities include:

Pre-check in condo inspection by our attentive staff
Personal "Aloha" upon your arrival
Full concierge and activity service
Gift pack of elite bath amenities
Luxury bed linens and towels

Why Us
With over 25 years of combined experience managing South Maui vacation condos in the Kihei, Wailea and Makena areas, we have earned our reputation as experts in Hawaii vacations. No one knows Maui like we do. It's the rare combination of quality and service that sets Ali'i Resorts apart. We work hard to elevate our brand to be the top vacation rental company on Maui. We maintain our 5 star Trip Advisor rating by keeping a full staff who strives to exceed your expectations for escape, and deliver your vacation accommodations with ease and satisfaction. We are your personal concierge and will work with you prior to your arrival to plan a range of services, activities, experiences, and excursions - be it a week of action and adventure or a complete relaxation. Come see us soon and let our ohana create a vacation of dreams for you and your family.

host_about: Jacob and I live in the attached home with our cat and 2 roommates. Airbnb has played a major role in my life, my father ran a hostel when I was a teenager until Covid hit, and now I run my own Airbnb with my partner Jacob. Our airbnb was converted from my childhood bedroom, and we hope you will feel as comfy and cozy as I did! I've always lived in Hawaii, worked as a tour guide and park ranger, and am always happy to share my insights with you!

name: The Rainforest Room
host_about:
ALOHA & WELCOME,

Thank you very much for viewing our various accommodations. Our accommodations are located along the lush and tropical Hamakua Coast, 15 miles north of Hilo.
I am  Akiko Masuda, a 3rd generation Japanese woman, born in Honolulu in the 40’s, long before freeways, shopping malls, email, Blackberrys, and cell phones. I have been a writer of children's books, student of tai chi, hula, and zen meditation,  I am a storyteller, hostess, housekeeper, and love caring for our gardens and fruit trees with our weedwhacker and leaf blower. I am the president of the WAILEA VILLAGE HISTORIC PRESERVATION COMMUNITY. I have been living in Wailea Village since' 91, and at that time, was the first person  to buy in this quiet, peaceful country village in 35 years.  Please come and discover the peace and kindness here.

name: 1 Bedroom Villa - Westin Ka'anapali
host_about:
I am a mother of two who lives her life by the 3 Fs: food, fitness and film.  My husband and I live in the San Francisco Bay Area, but love the snow and the beach, hence we have the Tahoe place and a place in Panama City Beach.  My husband's happy place in hitting flow on the slopes.  Mine is soaking in Vitamin D while hearing the waves in the back ground.  We feel very fortunate to be able to share both these places with you.  

Our kids are also into travel.  They have traveled to as many different countries as I have.  Our repeat favorites are New York, Portugal and Nicaragua.    When we travel, we love to stay at Airbnbs.  We want our guests to be as happy as we have been at previous stays.  Please reach out to us, at any point, if something is not to your liking.

host_about:
Ali'i is Hawaiian for "royalty," and we strive to live up to our name by giving each of our guests the royal treatment. Amenities include:

Pre-check in condo inspection by our attentive staff
Personal "Aloha" upon your arrival
Full concierge and activity service
Gift pack of elite bath amenities
Luxury bed linens and towels

Why Us
With over 25 years of combined experience managing South Maui vacation condos in the Kihei, Wailea and Makena areas, we have earned our reputation as experts in Hawaii vacations. No one knows Maui like we do. It's the rare combination of quality and service that sets Ali'i Resorts apart. We work hard to elevate our brand to be the top vacation rental company on Maui. We maintain our 5 star Trip Advisor rating by keeping a full staff who strives to exceed your expectations for escape, and deliver your vacation accommodations with ease and satisfaction. We are your personal concierge and will work with you prior to your arrival to plan a range of services, activities, experiences, and excursions - be it a week of action and adventure or a complete relaxation. Come see us soon and let our ohana create a vacation of dreams for you and your family.

name: Hawaiian Beaches Homestay 5-mins walk to the Sea
host_about: My partner Amanda & I love to learn, travel, & share the journey with wonderful people along the way.  We cultivate peace, harmony & health within ourselves each day through pure diet and exercise and enjoy sharing it others.  When I am home in Hawai'i, I serve as President and teacher at the Hawaii Tai Chi & Chinese Language Institute.  Some of my favorite places on Earth are Hawaii, Thailand, Taiwan, Bali, Kyoto, Okinawa and Sweden.  We enjoy meditation, yoga, exercise, dance, eating delicious fruits and vegetables, and making raw vegan Chocolate.

name: Paniolo: King, Pvt entrance, kitchenette:
host_about:
Aloha!  After I retired from teaching my husband and I decided to open up our house for travelers since we live in a pretty spectacular place having an active volcano in our back yard and just 1 miles from the Hawaii Volcanoes National Park. The weather is just fine here ~ not hot & tropical but a cool and misty rainforest. No A/C needed!

When we travel and staying in hotels we call it our new form of camping. We understand the ups and downs of traveling and attemp to make your stay with us as comfortable as possible. If you need anything you can always ask us ~ toiletries, jackets, flashlights, information, etc. Just let  us know and we can usually accommodate you.

name: A Bridge
host_about:
Hi,

I look forward to sharing my home with you and ensuring you a pleasant stay. I have travelled extensively, both domestically and internationally and enjoy cultural exchanges. I also enjoy tennis, biking, hiking, swimming and dancing.

name: Waikiki Movie Theme Studio *2Queen*
Vacation At its Finest! Elegant King Swimming Pool
Westin Ka’anapali ocean villa 1BR ocean view
host_about:
Hawaii. Costa Rica. Jamaica. Bahamas. Yellowstone Park, etc... At the end of one trip, I'm just counting until the next excursion somewhere exciting.  I can't live without traveling. It's in my nomadic nature to roam and never stay in one place.  From food to culture to natural wonders, I love and desire the flavors of the world on my tongue, I love and desire to be immersed in a wholly different culture, and I want to see, hear and feel the natural wonders that surround us. With my loving husband and my two boys we travel at every opportunity and we enjoy snowboarding, surfing, sightseeing. We are fond of Hawaii and have been to three of the islands (Oahu, Maui, Kauai) more times than we can count. 
As a Host on AirBnb, we offer where we go and where we have been so we know what our Guests might experience during their stay. As a result, we have the highest confidence that our Guests' stay will be a truly wonderful experience. 

Aloha and Mahalo,
Abby Heo

name: Comfort and Convenience! 2 Beautiful Units, Pool
2 Private Rooms for 2 Travel Nurses
host_about:
Aloha kākou! Salut! こんにちは! I am a local "hapa" (half Okinawan, half French).

I started out as an RN, wandered into the U. Of Hawai'i faculty system, and then... fell in love with teaching, learning, and educational design; especially alternative and web-based solutions.

My passions are endless: mixed media art, reading, technology, knitting, power tools, gardening, skiing, hiking, biking, camping, travel, volunteerism, baseball, Broadway, cooking, entertaining and TGIF's!

After spending most of my life in the islands and in empty-nest mode, I am designing the second half to explore mainland opportunities and travel more. 

I have always loved having a "home" in the islands to welcome mainland, inter-island, and international family and friends. Air B&B is the perfect opportunity to being able to welcome and host them in our now empty rooms, enabling everyone to enjoy all of what we islanders love about living here.

With Hawai'i's new short stay accommodation laws, we are only able to host 30-day or longer reservations. However, this does not affect our typical long-staying guests who come to the island for graduate program rotations, intern or externships, travel medical staff contracts, sabbaticals, grandparent month-long visits, etc.

Our goal is to provide a turnkey furnished and supplied island home for your 30-99 day time on O'ahu so that all you need to fly over with are your carryon of clothes and cell phone.

Please know, under the current pandemic circumstances, we are following all the federal, state, county, city and AirBnB mandates and policies along with our own home requirements to help all of us be good global and Honolulu citizens. Please send me a inquiry to run by your plans with me to consult with the most current policies.

Our goal is to provide a turnkey furnished and supplied island home for your 30-99 day time on O'ahu so that all you need to fly over with are your carryon of clothes and cell phone.

Please know, under the current pandemic circumstances, we are following all the federal, state, county, city and AirBnB mandates and policies along with our own home requirements to help all of us be good global and Honolulu citizens. Please send me a inquiry to run by your plans with me to consult with the most current policies.

host_about:
I have been in the vacation rental business since 2016 with over 20 years of experience in real estate, insurance, and property management. My family and I run several units on the beautiful island of Kauai. I enjoy scuba diving, kayaking, paddle boarding, and hiking. 

It has been one of my greatest joys to be able to do business in Kauai due to the friendly residents, how easy it is to get around, and the numerous island activities. I love getting to communicate with guests through platforms such as Airbnb. It makes my day to know that you are enjoying a vacation or casual getaway to one of the most beautiful Hawaiian islands at my unit. 

I look forward to connecting with you and always try to do my best to accommodate to your needs. I am always available to you through my contact information and provide very quick responses. Extremely excited to offer you a wonderful, family-friendly, and unforgettable tropical getaway!

I am a writer living in Waikiki. I've traveled the world but always come home to Hawaii, the most beautiful place on Earth. The surrounding sea sustains and enriches my spirit. An avid jazz lover, I cannot live without the bebop rhythms of artists like Monk, Coltrane, Baker and Bird. Sarah Vaughn is my goddess! Because I write, I also read, mostly novels ... voraciously. Love films, classic or contemporary. The following is one of my favorite odes to life.
Religion says: The body is a sin.
Science says: The body is a machine.
Advertising says: The body is a business.
The Body says: I am a fiesta!
~Eduardo Galeano
